# Freight Invoice Analysis Pipeline

End-to-end Python + SQL pipeline for UPS GFF invoice data —
cleans, pivots, and aggregates charge-line data into
shipment-level reporting tables.

**Invoice period:** Oct 22 – Nov 28, 2025 | **623 packages** | **$4,056 total**

## Files

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `01_clean_and_pivot.py` | Cleans raw flat file → one row per shipment, adds calculated columns |
| `02_aggregations.py` | Produces summary tables by zone, state, region, accessorial |
| `01_shipment_pivot_logic.sql` | SQL equivalent of the pivot script (BigQuery / PostgreSQL ready) |
| `02_analysis_queries.sql` | KPI queries, zone distribution, accessorial breakdown, outlier detection |
| `Freight_Analysis_Workbook.xlsx` | Excel workbook: KPI dashboard, zone pivot, savings calculator |

## Key Metrics

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Total packages | 623 |
| Total invoice | $4,056.11 |
| Freight base | $2,896 (71%) |
| Fuel surcharge | $512 (12.6% — above avg) |
| Accessorials | $648 (16%) |
| Packages with extra charges | 46.5% |

## Tools

Python · pandas · SQL · Excel (openpyxl) · Zoho Analytics
